Title: Millennium Art Festival
Description: Located two blocks from Chicago’s bustling Millennium Park, the Millennium Art Festival returns to downtown Chicago’s iconic Michigan Avenue for its fifth year. More than 175,000 people visit the area daily for work or play at the Art Institute, Chicago Cultural Center or Millennium Park. Chicagoans and tourists patronize and love this big city show. The Festival opens to the public on Friday to reach the tremendous number of people who work in the area and welcomes visitors from near and far on Saturday and Sunday. The festival takes place right off Chicago’s famed Michigan Avenue on Lake Street, next to some of the most famous and tallest buildings in the world. Admission to the festival is free. Easy listening live music takes place throughout the weekend.
Times: Friday & Saturday, 11 am-6 pm; Sunday, 10 am-6 pm
Location:
Loop, 199 N Michigan Ave
Chicago, IL 60601
